-Century The making of the 'Cover of the Century']\n\n{{Dalek stories}}\n{{Doctor Who villains}}\n{{Dalek audios}}\n{{Dalek stage plays}}\n{{Dalek novels}}\n{{Doctor Who species}}\n{{Doctor Who}}\n\n[[Category:Daleks| ]]\n[[Category:Doctor Who races]]\n[[Category:Extraterrestrial supervillains]]\n[[Category:Fictional cyborgs]]\n[[Category:Fictional genetically engineered characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional extraterrestrial life forms]]\n[[Category:Fictional mass murderers]]\n[[Category:Fictional mutants]]\n[[Category:Fictional warrior races]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 1963]]\n[[Category:Galactic empires]]\n[[Category:Time travelers]]\n", "name_user": "Nevadawest", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePhysical characteristics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dalek"}
{"title_page": "List of Castlevania media", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Castlevania'' media}}\n[[File:Castlevania logo.png|thumb|right|256px|Logo of the ''Castlevania'' series]]\n''[[Castlevania]]'' is a [[List of video game franchises|video game series]] created and developed by [[Konami]]. The series debuted in Japan on September 26, 1986 with {{nihongo|''Akumaj\u014d Dracula''|\u60aa\u9b54\u57ce\u30c9\u30e9\u30ad\u30e5\u30e9|Akumaj\u014d Dorakyura|lit. \"Demon Castle Dracula\"}}, which was later released as ''[[Castlevania (1986 video game)|Castlevania]]'' in the United States (May 1, 1987) and [[PAL region|PAL]] (December 19, 1988). The series is one of Konami's most celebrated franchises, appearing on several best-of lists.<ref>{{cite web| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120617164708/http://pc.ign.com/articles/749/749073p5.html|archivedate=2012-06-17|url= http://pc.ign.com/articles/749/749073p5.html|title=The Top 25 Videogame Franchises|work=IGN|date=2010-07-07|accessdate=2013-02-02}}</ref> \n\n''Castlevania'' titles have been released on numerous different [[video game console]]s, [[handheld game console]]s, and [[personal computer]] platforms, several of which have been re-released on multiple platforms and included as part of compilation packages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamefaqs.gamespot.com/ps4/260120-castlevania-anniversary-collection/data|title=Castlevania Anniversary Collection Release Information for PlayStation 4 - GameFAQs|website=gamefaqs.gamespot.com|access-date=2019-07-17}}</ref> The series' characters have appeared in several other Konami games. There have been also numerous separately released music albums, initially by [[King Records (Japan)|King Records]], then primarily by [[Konami]].\n\n==Video games==\n{{Video game titles|\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article= Castlevania (1986 video game)\n|title= Castlevania\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|September 26, 1986|NA|May 1, 1987|EU|December 19, 1988}}\n|refs= <ref name=\"C-1986\">{{cite web|url=http://www.konami.jp/gs/game/dracula/product/1986.html| script-title=ja:\u60aa\u9b54\u57ce\u30c9\u30e9\u30ad\u30e5\u30e9\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u7dcf\u5408\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 \u2013 1986|language=Japanese|publisher = [[Konami]]| accessdate = 2007-09-05}}</ref><ref name=\"CastlevaniaNES\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/nes/action/akumajodracula/similar.html?mode=versions |title=Castlevania (NES) \u2013 Related Games |website=[[GameSpot]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525065701/https://www.gamespot.com/nes/action/akumajodracula/similar.html/?mode=versions |archive-date=25 May 2011 |url-status=dead |access-date=11 October 2007}}</ref>\n|release= 1986 \u2013 [[Family Computer Disk System]]<ref name=\"C-1986\"/><br>1987 \u2013 [[Nintendo Entertainment System]],<ref name=\"CastlevaniaNES\" /> [[Nintendo Vs. System]],<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.gamespot.com/arcade/action/vscastlevania/similar.html?mode=versions| title = Vs. Castlevania&nbsp;\u2013 Release Summary| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref> [[PlayChoice-10]]<br>1990 \u2013 [[Personal computer|Personal Computer]],<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/castlevania/similar.html?mode=versions| title = Castlevania (PC) \u2013 Release Summary| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref> [[Commodore 64]],<ref>{{cite web| title = Castlevania (Commodore 64) \u2013 Release Summary| url = http://www.gamespot.com/c64/action/castlevania/similar.html?mode=versionsand| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref> [[Amiga]]<ref>{{cite web| title = Castlevania (Amiga) \u2013 Release Summary| url = http://www.gamespot.com/amiga/action/castlevania/similar.html?mode=versions| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref><br>1993 \u2013 [[Nintendo Entertainment System|Family Computer]]<ref name=\"CastlevaniaNES\" /><br>2002 \u2013 [[Microsoft Windows]]<ref name=\"CastlevaniaAndContra\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/konamicollectorsscc/similar.html?mode=versions |title=Konami Collector's Series: Castlevania & Contra&nbsp;\u2013 Release Summary |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=2007-10-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525065930/http://www.gamespot.com/pc/action/konamicollectorsscc/similar.html?mode=versions |archivedate=2011-05-25 }}</ref><br>2004 \u2013 [[Mobile phone]],<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.gamespot.com/mobile/action/castlevania/similar.html?mode=versions| title = Castlevania (mobile) \u2013 Release Summary| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref> [[Game Boy Advance]]<ref>{{cite web| title = Classic NES Series: Castlevania&nbsp;\u2013 Release Summary| url = http://www.gamespot.com/gba/action/famicomminiakumajodracula/similar.html?mode=versions| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-10-11}}</ref><br>2007 \u2013 [[Virtual Console]]<ref>{{cite web| url = http://wii.ign.com/articles/784/784418p1.html| title = VC Mondays: 04/30/07| author = Matt Casamassina| date = 2007-04-30| work = IGN| accessdate = 2007-09-10| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070915054800/http://wii.ign.com/articles/784/784418p1.html#| archive-date = 2007-09-15| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n|notes= * Known in Japan as {{nihongo|''Akumaj\u014d Dracula''|\u60aa\u9b54\u57ce\u30c9\u30e9\u30ad\u30e5\u30e9|Akumaj\u014d Dorakyura|lit. \"Demon Castle Dracula\"}}.<ref name=\"C-1986\"/>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article= Vampire Killer\n|title= Vampire Killer\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|October 30, 1986|EU|1986|BRA|1986}}\n|refs= <ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.gamespot.com/msx/action/vampirekiller/index.html?tag=result;title;0| title = Akumajou Dracula for MSX&nbsp;\u2013 Release Summary| work = [[GameSpot]]| accessdate = 2007-09-06}}</ref><ref name=\"VampKill-CG\">{{cite web| url = http://castlevaniadungeon.net/games/vk.html| title = Vampire Killer (1986)| work = The Castlevania Dungeon| ac