arring Gaemon|work=Hardcore Gaming 101|access-date=February 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B0000650E3/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1361274503&sr=8-1|title=\u304c\u3093\u3070\u308c\u30b4\u30a8\u30e2\u30f3~\u6b21\u5143\u57ce\u306e\u60aa\u5922 [VHS]|publisher=Amazon|language=Japanese|accessdate=February 19, 2013}}</ref>\n|platform= OVA\n|notes= * An OVA of Konami's ''[[Goemon (series)|Legend of the Mystical Ninja]]'' series. It features a short parody based on ''Castlevania''.\n* It was released on [[VHS]] on 26th March, 1993. A 5th anniversary edition video case was also released in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://goemon.freehostia.com/Series_Info/Animation/goemonova.htm|title= Ganbare goemon : jigen shiro no akumu|accessdate= June 30, 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title=Akumaj\u014d Dracula: Akuma no Chi Chi no Akumu\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|June 9, 1992 \u2013 December 1, 1995}}\n|refs=<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www2u.biglobe.ne.jp/~kousyou/list/logout.html|title= List of LOGOUT volumes|language=Japanese|publisher=Biglobe|accessdate= June 27, 2013}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Novel]], [[Literary magazine]]\n|notes= * Published in the Japanese magazine LOGOUT from 1992 to 1995. Discontinued after magazine suspended publication.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bent.co.jp/main/personal/tzk/207/naiyo_fr.htm|script-title= ja:\u624b\u585a\u4e00\u90ce\u3000\u8457\u4f5c\u7269\uff3b\u5c0f\u8aac\uff06\u30b3\u30df\u30c3\u30af7|language= Japanese|publisher= Bent|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150923183553/http://www.bent.co.jp/main/personal/tzk/207/naiyo_fr.htm|archivedate= 2015-09-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://books.rakuten.co.jp/rb/9024826/|script-title=ja:\u60aa\u9b54\u306e\u8840\u8840\u306e\u60aa\u5922\uff081\uff09\u3000\u5c0f\u8aac\u60aa\u9b54\u57ce\u30c9\u30e9\u30ad\u30e5\u30e9 \u30ed\u30b0\u30a2\u30a6\u30c8\u5192\u967a\u6587|language= Japanese|publisher= Rakuten Books|accessdate= June 27, 2013}}</ref>\n* The story is written by Ichiro Tezuka and is illustrated by Masaki Takahashi.\n* The first few issues of the story were released in novelized form on February 22, 1994.\n* Tezuka stated that, while the novel was originally intended to be a novelization of ''[[Super Castlevania IV]]'', he decided to instead write a completely new story that was unrelated to the ''Castlevania'' storyline, although the characters are based upon those of the ''Castlevania'' series.\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title= Dracula X: Nocturne in the Moonlight\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|March 20, 1997}}\n|refs=<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2012/09/feature_the_making_of_castlevania_symphony_of_the_night|title= Making Of Castlevania: Symphony of the Night|author= Damien McFerran|date= September 3, 2013|accessdate= June 18, 2013}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Manga]]\n|notes= * Prelude to ''[[Castlevania: Symphony of the Night|Symphony of the Night]]''. The manga was available exclusively by pre-ordering the limited edition of ''Castlevania: Symphony of the Night''.\n* Story and artwork by [[Ayami Kojima]].\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title= Castlevania: The Belmont Legacy\n|date= {{Video game release|NA|2005}}\n|refs= <ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.comixology.com/Castlevania-1-The-Belmont-Legacy/digital-comic/JAN052820|title= Castlevania #1: The Belmont Legacy|publisher= [[comiXology]]|accessdate= June 27, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.comixology.com/Castlevania-5-The-Belmont-Legacy/digital-comic/MAY052810|title= Castlevania #5: The Belmont Legacy|publisher= [[comiXology]]|accessdate= June 27, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|isbn=1933239190|title= Castlevania: The Belmont Legacy|publisher= Amazon}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Graphic novel]]\n|notes= * The graphic novel is written by [[Marc Andreyko]] and illustrated by [[E. J. Su]]. It was published by [[IDW Publishing]] in five issues from March 30, 2005 to September 20,