ml|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121219065040/http://www11.ocn.ne.jp/~ocomplex/o-cvtxt.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=December 19, 2012|title=\u306f\u3058\u3081\u306b|work=OCN.ne.jp|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Mobile comic]]\n|notes= * Comic adaptation of ''[[Castlevania: Lament of Innocence|Lament of Innocence]]'' designed to be read on a cellphone.\n* 40 episodes of the comic were released.\n* Konami's mobile comic service \"Weekly Konami\" ended as of March 31, 2012. This comic can no longer be bought.\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title= Akumaj\u014d Dracula: Radio Chronicle\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|2008}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"Dracula Radio Chronicle Akumajo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.konami.jp/products/style_lc1657_8/|title=Dracula Radio Chronicle Akumajo |language=Japanese|publisher=Konami|accessdate=March 14, 2013}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Internet radio]], [[Compact disc|CD]]\n|notes= * Japanese language only internet radio program aired on Konami Station in 2008.\n* A radio drama ''Akumaj\u014d Dracula X: Tsuioku no Yas\u014dkyoku'', Castlevania: The Adventure ReBirth and Contra ReBirth OST, Castlevania Best Music Collections BOX were aired on the program.\n*A special limited edition of the radio drama was released on CD was published by Konami Style on March 24, 2010 in Japan.\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title= Akumaj\u014d Dracula X: Tsuioku no Yas\u014dkyoku\n|date= {{Video game release|JP|August \u2013 November 2008}}\n|refs=<ref name=\"Dracula Radio Chronicle Akumajo\"/>\n|platform= [[Internet radio]], [[Compact disc|CD]]\n|notes= * A radio drama based on ''Symphony of the Night'' and takes place shortly afterwards the events of the game.\n* Originally aired as a feature of Akumaj\u014d Dracula: Radio Chronicle from August to November 2008.\n* Released on [[Compact disc|CD]] on March 24, 2010.\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article=\n|title= Akumaj\u014d Dracula: Kabuchi no Tsuisoukyoku\n|date= S