 by Kevin S\u00e1nchez|work = Square Enix Music Online|accessdate = 2013-02-02}}</ref>\n|refs=\n|platform=[[Concert]]\n|notes=* The first concert based on ''Castlevania''.\n* Organized by David Westerlund and Erik Eklund. Performed by [[Michiru Yamane]] and Stockholm Youth Symphonic Orchestra.<ref name=\"CastlevaniaConcert1\">{{cite web| url = http://www.castlevaniaconcert.com/| title = Castlevania The Concert Official Site| work = Castlevania Concert| accessdate = 2009-12-10| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20091031061758/http://www.castlevaniaconcert.com/| archivedate = 2009-10-31}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article= Castlevania (TV series)\n|title= Castlevania\n|date= July 7, 2017\n|refs=\n|platform= [[Netflix]]\n|notes= *Animated series based on ''Castlevania III: Dracula's Curse''.\n*A second series started on October 26, 2018.\n* Featuring the voice of [[Richard Armitage (actor)|Richard Armitage]] as Trevor Belmont.\n* Written by comic book author, [[Warren Ellis]].<ref>{{cite web | author=Ellis, Warren | year=2006 | title=Castlevania | url=http://www.warrenellis.com/?p=3133 | work=WarrenEllis.com | accessdate=2007-08-02}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Video game titles/item\n|article= Castlevania #film\n|title= Castlevania\n|date= TBA, formerly cancelled\n|refs=<ref name=\"FilmCanceled\">{{cite web| url = http://kotaku.com/5271735/castlevania-movie-has-been-slayed| title = Castlevania Movie Has Been Slayed| first = Brian| last = Ashcraft| date = 2009-05-28| work = Kotaku| accessdate = 2009-07-14}}</ref><ref name=\"FilmCanceled-2\">{{cite web| url = http://www.1up.com/do/newsStory?cId=3174410| title = Castlevania Movie Cancelled| first = Anthony| last = Parisi| date = 2009-05-27| work = [[1UP.com]]| accessdate = 2009-07-14}}{{dead link|date=October 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=\"FilmRevived\">{{cite web| url = http://www.destructoid.com/sdcc-saw-director-bringing-castlevania-to-the-big-screen-141080.phtml| title = SAW director bringing Castlevania to the big screen| work=Destructoid| date = 2009-07-23| accessdate = 2009-07-23}}</ref>\n|platform= [[Film]]\n|notes= * The film was intended to be based on the video game series and focus on the origins of the main characters.<ref name=\"FilmCanceled-2\"/><ref name=\"white\">{{cite web| first = Michaeel| last = Fleming| url = http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117966892.html?categoryid=13&cs=1| title = White stakes out 'Castlevania'| work = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]| date = 2007-06-13| accessdate = 2007-06-14 }}</ref>\n* [[Paul W. S. Anderson]] was originally attached to write and direct the film, with filming planned to begin in Eastern Europe in 2006.<ref name=\"FilmCanceled\"/><ref name=\"FilmCanceled-2\"/>\n* Anderson later stepped down from directing and [[Sylvain White]] joined the project to direct and assist with the script.<ref name=\"FilmCanceled\"/>\n* After White left the project, a new director was not found and the project become indefinitely on hold.<ref name=\"FilmCanceled\"/><ref name=\"FilmCanceled-2\"/> James Wan (''[[Saw (2004 film)|Saw]]'', ''[[Dead Silence]]'') then took over the director's chair with Paul W.S. Anderson still producing the movie.<ref name=\"FilmRevived\"/>\n}}\n}}\n\n===Music albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width: 100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:50%;\" scope=\"col\"|Title\n! style=\"width:15%;\" scope=\"col\"|Release date\n! style=\"width:13%;\" scope=\"col\" data-sort- type=\"number\"|Length\n! style=\"width:30%;\" scope=\"col\"|Label\n! style=\"width:2%;\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref.\n|- style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| ''Konami Game Music Collection Volume 1''\n| {{dts|August 5, 1988}}\n| {{sort|5930|59:30}}\n|[[King Records (Japan)|King Records]]\n|<ref name=\"KGMCV1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.squareenixmusic.com/albums/k/konamicollection1.shtml |title=Konami Game Music Collection Vol